---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Headless Commerce Development"
  description="Build a faster, more flexible commerce experience with headless Shopify, Astro, Next.js, and API-driven integrations that improve speed, scalability, and conversion."
  keywords="headless commerce, commerce architecture, astro nextjs ecommerce, shopify hydrogen, wix headless"
>
  <section class="relative pt-36 pb-20 overflow-hidden bg-surface">
    <!-- Backlights -->
    <div class="absolute top-1/4 left-1/4 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-primary-maroon/10 rounded-full blur-[120px] pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(to_right,rgba(193,199,207,0.02)_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(to_bottom,rgba(193,199,207,0.02)_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:4rem_4rem] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 relative z-10">
      
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold text-primary-accent hover:text-white transition-colors uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-8 focus:outline-none">
        ← Back to Overview
      </a>

      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="max-w-[800px] mb-16">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-purple-500/20 bg-purple-500/5 text-[10px] font-bold text-purple-400 tracking-[0.1em] uppercase mb-4">
          The Performance Frontier
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          Headless Commerce. <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-secondary-silver via-white to-primary-accent bg-clip-text text-transparent">Decoupled Performance.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-secondary-silver leading-relaxed">
          Decouple a heavy, monolithic backend setup. By placing a custom Astro or Next.js static engine on the edge, we isolate the presentation layer from backend computations, maximizing conversion metrics.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Specs & Performance Highlights -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-20">
        <div class="p-6 border border-outline-ghost bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant/70 font-semibold block mb-2">Transition Metric</span>
          <span class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white block mb-1">0.4s Load Time</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-secondary-silver">Edge cached index and catalog layouts serving instant pixels.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 border border-outline-ghost bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant/70 font-semibold block mb-2">Web Vitals</span>
          <span class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white block mb-1">100 / 100 Score</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-secondary-silver">Perfect Lighthouse optimization for LCP, CLS, and TBT.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 border border-outline-ghost bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant/70 font-semibold block mb-2">Integration Sync</span>
          <span class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white block mb-1">Omnichannel API</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-secondary-silver">Connecting external ERP, warehouse data, and global CRM systems.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Content Grid -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-20">
        
        <!-- Left Column: Key Pillars -->
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">Decoupled Engineering Capabilities</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-default bg-primary-maroon/20 border border-primary-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-accent shrink-0 font-bold text-sm">01</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white mb-2">Next.js & Astro Frontends</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed">
                  Building reactive layouts using Next.js Server Components or Astro Static Rendering. Frontends compile to static HTML/JS bundles hosted globally on Vercel or Netlify.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-default bg-primary-maroon/20 border border-primary-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-accent shrink-0 font-bold text-sm">02</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white mb-2">Wix & Shopify Headless APIs</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed">
                  Pairing modern UI frontends with established backend databases. We pipe cart states, payment checkout tokens, and products catalogs via GraphQL APIs, securing transaction flows.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-default bg-primary-maroon/20 border border-primary-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-accent shrink-0 font-bold text-sm">03</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white mb-2">Edge-Optimized Infrastructures</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed">
                  Configuring edge caches, database replication, and CDN routing logic so global visitors experience identical sub-second load speeds regardless of localization.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Column: Specifications Detail Card -->
        <div class="p-8 border border-outline-ghost/40 bg-surface-container rounded-lg relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-24 h-24 bg-primary-maroon/10 rounded-full blur-2xl pointer-events-none"></div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs border-b border-outline-ghost/20 pb-4">Architecture & API Specifications</h3>
          
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">API Integration</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">GraphQL, Restful Webhooks</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Framework Layer</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">React, Astro Core, Next.js</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Checkout Tunnel</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">Shopify Checkout SDK / Wix E-com</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Data Fetching</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">CDN Edge Deploy</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">Vercel Edge Network, Cloudflare</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          
          <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-surface-container-low border border-outline-ghost/50 rounded-default text-xs text-on-surface-variant">
            <strong class="text-white block mb-1">Monolith-to-Headless Migration:</strong> We specialize in migrating legacy, slow monoliths (old Magento, WooCommerce installations) into snappy headless engines, avoiding downtime.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Action Footer -->
      <div class="p-8 border border-primary-accent/20 bg-primary-maroon/5 rounded-lg flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-1">Ready to explore headless performance?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-secondary-silver">Consult our engineering team to draft a custom decoupled blueprint.</p>
        </div>
        <a 
          href="/#contact" 
          class="w-full sm:w-auto px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-primary-maroon border border-primary-accent/40 rounded-default glow-btn-primary hover:text-white transition-all shadow-lg text-center"
        >
          Book Strategy Call
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 md:py-28 bg-surface border-t border-outline-ghost/30">
    <div class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 max-w-[760px] mx-auto">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-primary-accent/20 bg-primary-maroon/10 text-[10px] font-bold text-primary-accent tracking-[0.16em] uppercase mb-5">
          Headless FAQs
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-5">
          Headless Commerce Questions Answered
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-secondary-silver leading-relaxed">
          These FAQs address common search intent around decoupled architecture, migration, performance, and API-driven commerce experiences.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4">
        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7" open>
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">What is headless commerce and why do brands use it?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Headless commerce separates the storefront experience from the commerce backend so brands can deliver faster, more flexible experiences while integrating with modern APIs and custom frontend frameworks.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Is headless commerce better for performance and SEO?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            In many cases, yes. A decoupled frontend can be optimized for edge delivery, faster rendering, and stronger Core Web Vitals, which directly improves both user experience and search visibility.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Can you migrate from a monolithic ecommerce setup to headless?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Yes. We design phased migration strategies that preserve existing data, minimize risk, and gradually transition the storefront to a modern headless architecture without unnecessary downtime.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Which frameworks are best for headless storefronts?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Astro and Next.js are common choices depending on the project goals. Astro is excellent for static, high-speed content-heavy storefronts, while Next.js supports richer app-like product experiences and dynamic rendering needs.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is headless commerce and why do brands use it?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Headless commerce separates the storefront experience from the commerce backend so brands can deliver faster, more flexible experiences while integrating with modern APIs and custom frontend frameworks."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is headless commerce better for performance and SEO?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "In many cases, yes. A decoupled frontend can be optimized for edge delivery, faster rendering, and stronger Core Web Vitals, which directly improves both user experience and search visibility."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you migrate from a monolithic ecommerce setup to headless?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. We design phased migration strategies that preserve existing data, minimize risk, and gradually transition the storefront to a modern headless architecture without unnecessary downtime."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which frameworks are best for headless storefronts?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Astro and Next.js are common choices depending on the project goals. Astro is excellent for static, high-speed content-heavy storefronts, while Next.js supports richer app-like product experiences and dynamic rendering needs."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
</script>
